venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Sin City is an inclusive venue that welcome Deaf and disabled people. From the street level there is a ramp into the main entrance, providing level access to the box office. There are toilets located on this level. From here there are 21 steps into the main room. There are an additional 18 steps up to room 2. There is also an additional entrance to room 2 from the street which is up 22 steps. BOOKABLE ACCESS FACILITIES + HOW TO APPLY (IF APPLICABLE) Personal Assistant tickets: If you require a PA ticket, please contact us and we can arrange this for you. Accessible viewing area: If you require a seat, please call up in advance. In the main room, there is the option of booth seating up 3 steps that we can reserve for you. An alternative to this is a stool with a back support and high table that can also be reserved. TRAVEL GUIDE AND ARRIVAL GUIDE There is accessible parking available at the Oxford Street/Grand Theatre car park, which is 150 metres away. There are 22 number of accessible spaces in this car park. Taxis are able to drop off right outside the venue and there is a taxi office over the road, around 50 metres away. Swansea Quadrant bus station is 320 metres away and Swansea station 965 metres away. TOILETS The nearest accessible toilet is located at Potters Wheel which is 35 metres away, and open until 1am. We have an agreement that our customers are able to use this toilet. CUSTOMERS WITH MEDICAL REQUIREMENTS We welcome any customers who may need to bring food, drink, medication or medical equipment to manage a medical condition. ASSISTANCE DOGS We welcome assistance dogs into the venue. If you intend to bring an assistance dog, please let us know in advance to make necessary arrangements.

The  Relentless Garage takes the needs of disabled customers very seriously and actively encourages people of all abilities to attend the events scheduled at their venue. Though built in Victorian times, the building has been modernized to allow wheelchair access via front of house to the Ground floor level (please note there is no direct backstage disabled access). On the evening of an event, we do advise disabled customers to arrive at the venue 15 minutes prior to doors, ideally accompanied by a companion over 18 years old who will be admitted free of charge.

The free companion ticket is available to patrons who are registered disabled. Both the ticket to be paid for and the free companion ticket needs to be booked in advance.

Once the venue has confirmed availability you can purchase a ticket through our event listings page or by phoning 0844 847 2472 and the venue will arrange for a free personal assistant ticket to be available for patrons who are registered disabled. A photocopy/scan of one of the following official documents (dated within the past 12 months) will enable you to qualify for a free personal assistant ticket. Please do not send the original copy. Front page of DLA letter Front page of Attendance Allowance letter Evidence that registered severely sight impaired Recognised Assistance Dog ID card Please note that a ticket will not be sent out to your PA prior to the event. They will be available for collection at the venue Box Office when you arrive. On the evening of the event, we advise disabled customers and those with specific access requirements to arrive at the venue 15 minutes prior to the doors opening, accompanied, where required and approved in advance by a personal assistant over 18 years of age who will be admitted free of charge. boxOfficeInfo.phoneNumberDetail: Accessible tickets can be booked online, or you can call 0141 576 3230 (replaces 0800 952 0110 temporarily) (open Mon-Fri 9am-2pm). Need help with your order? If you booked online via Ticketmaster, you can view their help section here or access 24hr support for specific orders in your online account. More information about how to access your online account is available here. If you booked over the phone, or in person with SEC, please email booking.enquiries@sec.co.uk or use our contact page
boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: The Box office opens at 3pm on the day of the event and closes 15 mins after the main act takes to stage, unless otherwise stated. Tickets can be purchased online 24 hours a day at www.ovohydro.com (powered by Ticketmaster).
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: Mastercard/Visa/AMEX/Cash
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Tickets can be collected from the SEC Centre box office on the day of the event from the advertised doors opening time. Please take the credit card used to make the booking and your Ticketmaster reference number

venues.parkingDetail: The multi-storey is operated by City Parking LLP. A map and directions are here. Onsite pay machines are on the ground floor, or level 2 (walkway level) of the car park. Payment can be made by cash or credit/debit card on arrival or before departure. Tariff Rates in the multi-storey Monday to Sunday are: 0-1 hour 5.50 1-12 hours 11 12-13 hours 16 13-24 Hours 22 Further information is available from the operators website. The multi-storey has a height restriction of 2m. Drivers with vehicles over 2m should report to the Gatehouse to the west of the campus (accessed via Stobcross Road) in the first instance and you will be directed to an available space.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Accessible tickets are available to book online, but for larger or more complex groups, please call our dedicated accessible booking line on 0800 952 0110. For more information on accessible service visit the venue website, call the above number or email info@sec.co.uk SEC are committed to making a visit to the Scottish Event Campus an enjoyable experience for everyone. The venue is easily accessible for visitors with mobility difficulties and accessibility needs and currently holds a Gold Award from Attitude is Everything. The main doors in the SEC Armadillo have been widened to provide easier access for wheelchairs. The upper levels are accessible by lift. Entry to The Armadillo via the main doors are wide for accessible users There is an induction loop system on level 0 of the venue for visitors with hearing impairments.

generalInfo.generalRule: The following policies apply to most events, but each event may differ, so please check the venue website event page for specific event policies. For full details of all venue policies see the venue website FAQs page. Searching and security All bags and visitors may be searched when entering the venue. Bags larger than A3 size (30cm x 42cm) are not be permitted at live events. Exit and Re-Entry You may leave and re-enter the venue during the event, as long as you present your ticket for scanning each time. Cameras In general audio and video recording equipment and professional cameras (SLR types and those with detachable lenses) are not permitted into events. However, small non-professional cameras and phone cameras may be permitted, unless otherwise specified by the event organiser. Special Effects Special effects are used at many events and are controlled by the touring production team. If the use of certain effects concern you, or you would like further information on effects that may be used at a specific show, please email the venue. Assistance Dogs The SEC welcomes visitors with assistance dogs. We would ask that assistance dogs are clearly identifiable around the campus.
generalInfo.childRule: All children must have a valid ticket for an event, with the exception of babes in arms (under 12 months) who may sit on a parent or guardians knee, unless otherwise stated by the event promoter. We have a small number of booster seats available to borrow for events in the SEC Armadillo. These are allocated on a first come first served basis and may be fully allocated at popular family events. If a booster seat is essential to your visit, we would encourage you to bring your own to avoid disappointment. It is the venues recommendation that children under five should not attend concerts or events, other than those specifically aimed at younger visitors, i.e. childrens shows.

venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: The venue is accessible for wheelchair users. Customers requiring access to the disabled area at O2 Academy Islington must contact the venue on 020 7288 4410 between 10am and 5pm (Monday - Friday) or email disabledbookings@o2academyislington.co.uk with requirements so the appropriate provisions can be made. Customers will then be required to purchase ticket(s) for the event through any agency to confirm their booking. The disabled access area is not static and is created on a show by show basis depending upon the number of people requiring access. If you are registered disabled you are entitled to be accompanied by a free carer so please take this into consideration when booking your ticket(s).

generalInfo.generalRule: No video cameras or recording devices allowed. Current licensing laws are strictly enforced. Right of admission is reserved. Tickets are non-refundable or transferable. Ticket holders may be subject to search - any persons found in possession of weapons of any description may be refused entry and/or the items seized will be logged and handed over to the police. A no re-admission policy is strictly enforced. No bottles, cans, alcohol or food may be brought into the venue. No illegal substances may be brought into or taken on the premises. Any one caught in possession of such substances will be ejected from the premises and may be reported to the police. Only customers in possession of a valid ticket will be admitted into the venue. Lost, stolen or misplaced tickets will not be replaced. Ticket holders may be subject to continuous sound levels that may cause potential damage to hearing. Ticket holders may be exposed to strobe lighting. Ticket holders consent to any filming and sound recordings as members of the audience.
